ping ground of nomads’.","Indian: topographic name from Sanskrit <i>aranya</i> ‘grove’. This is one of the ten surnames borne by members of the Dasnami order of monks, whose name is based on the place where the sadhu who funded the clan was initiated."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":0,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":45,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":118,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice de Raan was born in 1337, in Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England, her father, Walter de Raan, was 32 and her mother, Margery Blankett, was 25. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas de la Grove."},"et":{"1337–":"1337–Surnud","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1305–1372":"1305–1372","1312–Female":"1312–Surnud","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","Abt 1361":"umbes 1361","1455":"1455","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","1372":"1372","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1337–":"1337–Kuollut","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1305–1372":"1305–1372","1312–Female":"1312–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","Abt 1361":"noin 1361","1455":"1455","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","1372":"1372","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1337–":"1337–Décédée","1337–Female":"1337–Décédée","1338–Male":"1338–Décédé","1361–Female":"1361–Décédée","1305–1372":"1305–1372","1312–Female":"1312–Décédée","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","Abt 1361":"environ 1361","1455":"1455","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","1372":"1372","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Alice de Raan est